Rating: 1
Sorry folks... this is not the real deal! I'm 100% Greek, and I am here to tell you that Greeks don't even know what sour cream is! And we don't put lemon juice in our tzatziki either -- maybe a dash of vinegar, but that's it! Might explain why some think it is too sour..... To make the real deal you need Greek yogurt. Trader Joe's sells it, and even has the FAGE Greek brand. FYI -- you can cut Greek yogurt with a knife -- that is how thick it is. Also be sure to strain your cucumber. And my personal preference.... Triple or quadruple the garlic!!! Good for you and TASTY!!!! Kali orexi!(bon appetite in Greek....:)

