Rating: 0
Love this dish. I use it with shredded cukes as a sauce over grilled lamb, or with sliced/cubed cukes and less yogurt as a side dish. Perfect for summer. To add to previous reviews...I think regular (not non-fat) yogurt is important, but that said, "all natural" won't work (too thin). I like to drain my yogurt, in fact, I make the whole thing a day ahead. Make sure you use fresh garlic, and cut out any green shoot growing out the middle of the clove (it tastes funny). I like to salt my sliced cukes and drain them in the sink for thirty minutes, that really reduces bitterness. I still think fresh dill is important -- cleaner taste. And finally, agree with previous reviewer, you MUST add a shot of good quality Olive Oil at the very end.

