This is DELICIOUS tzatziki! Usually I just buy mine at the supermarket, but it was never very complex, so when this recipe came my way I decided to give it a shot. I actually planned an entire meal around this dip-- so needless to say, I am glad it turned out so well. Based on other reviews, I started with one clove of garlic, tasted it, then added another... and another. I really think 3 cloves is the perfect amount, but Bon Appetit may have wanted to publish a dip recipe with a more subtle garlic flavor. I also planned on serving this the day it was made, but due to time constraints, had to postpone the meal an extra day. The flavors melded so well, I will always make this 1 day in advance from now on. I was unsure of whether or not to use nonfat yogurt, but since I don't have cheesecloth, I went for it, and it was great. Just like everyone said, there is no need to drain overnight at all. I served the tzatziki with pork souvlaki, couscous, grilled pita, and a Greek salad. Delicious and memorable.

